Linköp. las. barnavd. s. å., las :’läk. där 3’1-44, ’skolläk. v. lärov. i Linköp. 32-44, överläk. v. med. avd. å Barnsjukh. i Gbg sed. 44, sjukh. styresman 45, lär. i b ar nav. v. läroanst. f. barnmorskor i Gbg sed. 45. translated: Åkerren, Olof Yngve Carl, senior physician, Gothenburg, b. 9/6/96 in Umeå to county councilor Olof Å. and Gerda Ahlander. M. 21 with Carin Prytz. Children: Bengt b. 22, JD, attaché, Bo b. 25, medical student, Gunilla b. 31, Ingrid and Kerstin b. 36. — Graduated in Västerås 13’, Bachelor of Medicine 17, licensed doctor 22 and Doctor of Medicine 34 in Uppsala. Trainee and assistant at the pathology department in Uppsala 19-20 and 21-22, resident doctor at Umeå hospital's pathology and medical department 23-24, second and first assistant physician at Garn army hospital's medical department in Stockholm 24-26, acting assistant physician at the general children's hospital's pediatric clinic for six months in 26-27, trainee at the pediatric clinic in Uppsala 27-29, also acting senior physician for six months, trainee at the medical clinic in Uppsala 30, licensed doctor at Linköping hospital's pediatric department the same year, resident doctor there 31-44, school physician at the high school in Linköping 32-44, senior physician at the medical department at Children's Hospital in Gothenburg since 44, hospital administrator 45, lecturer in infant care at the midwifery school in Gothenburg since 45. Battalion physician in the reserve in Fik 23, in Fik 25-30, in the reserve since 30. Studied abroad in 24, 29 and 32-33. Wrote about 36 research papers in pediatrics and internal medicine.
